          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "It’s 2022 and some people are just now figuring for at least the past two years we’ve been dealing with a huge upswing in car thefts pretty much everywhere. Sure, some areas are worse than others, like if you live in Detroit or Milwaukee we genuinely feel bad for your plight. But you would think people in Philadelphia would have caught on to this crime spree a little bit sooner. A local report highlights how the public outrage has only recently bubbled over, so they’re late to the party.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
